# Webasto Pages — Implementation Plan

Two standalone landing pages dedicated to Webasto, replacing the single generic service-data entry with rich, purpose-built pages.

## Proposed Changes

### Page Architecture Decision

Both pages will be **standalone HTML files** (not driven by [services-data.js](file:///e:/Antigravity/AntigravityAgents/mr.car/ru/services/services-data.js)) because they have unique sections that go far beyond the generic service template (5-step process, testimonials, FAQ accordion, when-to-repair matrix, etc.). They reuse the site's shared [style.css](file:///e:/Antigravity/AntigravityAgents/mr.car/style.css), navbar/footer, and FAB — same as the existing [service.html](file:///e:/Antigravity/AntigravityAgents/mr.car/ru/services/service.html) template.

---

### New Webasto CSS Components

#### [MODIFY] [style.css](file:///e:/Antigravity/AntigravityAgents/mr.car/style.css)

Add new CSS classes under `wb-*` namespace appended to the end of the file (after the existing `sd-*` service detail styles):

| Component | Classes | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Inline CTA banner** | `.wb-cta-inline` | Accent-bordered block with "Broneeri aeg" button within content flow |
| **5-step process timeline** | `.wb-process`, `.wb-step` | Numbered vertical timeline with icon + title + description |
| **Benefits grid** | `.wb-benefits` | 3-column icon cards for Mr.Car advantages |
| **FAQ accordion** | `.wb-faq`, `.wb-faq__item`, `.wb-faq__q`, `.wb-faq__a` | Accordion with expand/collapse, keyboard accessible |
| **Testimonials** | `.wb-testimonials`, `.wb-testimonial` | Bordered cards with name/date/text |
| **When-to-repair cards** | `.wb-decision`, `.wb-decision__card` | Two side-by-side cards (green = repair now, yellow = can wait) |
| **Consequences warning** | `.wb-warning` | Alert-style block with icon + text |

All components follow the existing Technical Brutalism design tokens (`--bg-main`, `--accent-primary`, `--border-grid`, etc.) and the M3 accessibility baseline from the user rules.

---

### Page 1: Webasto diagnostika ja remont

#### [NEW] [webasto-diagnostika.html](file:///e:/Antigravity/AntigravityAgents/mr.car/ee/services/webasto-diagnostika.html)

**URL:** `/services/webasto-diagnostika` (via Netlify rewrite)

**Sections (top → bottom):**

1. **Hero** — Full-width background, H1 "Webasto diagnostika ja remont Tallinnas", lead text, CTA button
2. **Booking form** — "Broneeri aeg Webasto diagnostikaks" with fields: nimi, auto reg.nr, telefon, email, probleemi kirjeldus
3. **5-step process** — Kontakt → Diagnostika → Tagasiside → Remont → Kontroll ja tagastus
4. **Benefits** — Icon grid: spetsialiseerumine, asukoht, ausad hinnad, garantii
5. **Testimonials** — 2–3 client review cards
6. **Google Map** — Kopli 82a iframe (grayscale filter, matching existing)
7. **Final CTA** — Repeat phone + form + address block
8. **Footer** — Identical to existing pages

**SEO:**
- Title: `Webasto diagnostika ja remont Tallinnas — Mr.Car Autoteenindus`
- JSON-LD: `AutoRepair` + [Service](file:///e:/Antigravity/AntigravityAgents/mr.car/ee/services/service.html#396-400) + `FAQPage`

---

### Page 2: Webasto sümptomid ja vead

#### [NEW] [webasto-sumptomid.html](file:///e:/Antigravity/AntigravityAgents/mr.car/ee/services/webasto-sumptomid.html)

**URL:** `/services/webasto-sumptomid` (via Netlify rewrite)

**Sections (top → bottom):**

1. **Hero** — H1 "Webasto sümptomid ja vead", lead text, CTA to diagnostika page
2. **Inline CTA** — "Tunned ära mõne neist sümptomitest? Broneeri diagnostika"
3. **Symptoms grid** — 7 symptoms in brutalist grid (icon + text): ei käivitu, ei soojenda, kustub ise, müra, suits/lõhn, veateated, auto ei käivitu külmaga
4. **Consequences** — "Miks ei tohi remonti edasi lükata" warning block + list
5. **When-to-repair cards** — 2-column: "Millal tasub remontida" (green) vs "Millal võib oodata" (yellow)
6. **Mr.Car benefits** — Why choose this workshop (same as page 1, linked)
7. **FAQ accordion** — 5–6 Q&A pairs about battery, safety, salon disassembly, scheduling, preventive checks
8. **Final CTA** — Phone, form link to page 1, address
9. **Footer** — Identical

**SEO:**
- Title: `Webasto sümptomid ja vead — Millal pöörduda Mr.Car Tallinnas?`
- JSON-LD: `FAQPage`

---

### Routing

#### [MODIFY] [netlify.toml](file:///e:/Antigravity/AntigravityAgents/mr.car/netlify.toml)

Add two new redirect rules for the standalone pages:

```toml
[[redirects]]
  from = "/services/webasto-diagnostika"
  to = "/ee/services/webasto-diagnostika.html"
  status = 200

[[redirects]]
  from = "/services/webasto-sumptomid"
  to = "/ee/services/webasto-sumptomid.html"
  status = 200
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> These must be placed **before** the existing wildcard `/services/:slug` rule, otherwise the wildcard will match first.

---

### Services Data Update

#### [MODIFY] [services-data.js](file:///e:/Antigravity/AntigravityAgents/mr.car/ee/services/services-data.js)

Update the existing Webasto entry's slug from `webasto-remont` to `webasto-diagnostika` (since the standalone page now handles that URL). The entry in [services-data.js](file:///e:/Antigravity/AntigravityAgents/mr.car/ru/services/services-data.js) will **remain** so the sidebar navigation and mega-menu continue to show Webasto. The slug will link directly to the new standalone page.

---

### Cross-linking

- Page 1 (diagnostika) links to Page 2 (sümptomid) in its intro: "Loe lähemalt Webasto sümptomite kohta →"
- Page 2 (sümptomid) links to Page 1 (diagnostika) via multiple CTAs: "Broneeri diagnostika →"

